# C-PHI — Protected Health Information Boundaries

**Non-negotiable.** PHI must not appear in notification payloads, log lines, LLM system prompts, or `audit_log.payload` JSON. PHI may travel **only** in designated channels listed below.

This rule **extends** (does not replace) existing `.cursorrules` §1.1 RSC/PHI boundary rules for `apps/web`.

## Allowed PHI channels

| Channel | PHI allowed? | Notes |
|---|---|---|
| LLM **user** message (analyze-intake) | **Yes** | Step-1 answers as user content; system prompt stays PHI-free |
| LLM **system** prompt / prompt `.md` files | **No** | `services/analysis-engine/prompts/*` must be PHI-free |
| `audit_log.payload` | **No** | Use entity IDs, action names, gap keys — never field values |
| Application logs (`console`, structured logger) | **No** | Log IDs, actions, status codes; redact or omit content |
| Notification payload types | **No** | Structurally must not accept PHI fields (DoD-7) |
| URL paths / query strings | **No** | Token in path only; never patient name or health data in URLs |
| Client Components / browser storage | **No** | Existing rule: PHI renders server-side only |
| Third-party APIs (AssemblyAI, Textract) | **Only if** `baa_verified=true` | Block when BAA not verified (TR-2) |

## API-1 — unauthenticated PHI surface

`GET /api/intake/[token]` is the **only** unauthenticated endpoint returning patient-linked intake state. Token: 128-bit, hashed at rest, TTL, rate-limit, lockout (SEC-18).

## Trusted facts for generation

`lib/prompt/format-timeline-for-prompt.ts` excludes unconfirmed `source: ai` fields until clinician-confirmed (DoD-10).

## Failure modes (do not do these)

1. **Embedding example patient narratives in system prompts** — use generic schema instructions instead.
2. **`console.error(error, requestBody)`** where `requestBody` contains intake answers.
3. **Storing transcript snippets or symptom text in `audit_log.payload`** for "debuggability".
4. **Sending PHI to AssemblyAI/Textract** when `baa_verified` is false.
